<l>āṟeṉ kiḷavi mutaṉī ṭummē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The first [syllable] of the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">āṟu</foreign> ' six ' will be lengthened [be-</l>
<l>fore vowels].<note place="foot">I.e. according to the general rule, the initial <foreign xml:lang="ta">ā</foreign>
          of <foreign xml:lang="ta">āṟu</foreign> is shortened ; before a vowel, it resumes its
          original long form, eg. <foreign xml:lang="ta">āṟu + akal &gt; āṟakal.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
